The course aims to give an introduction into the historical development and the present stage of South Estonian languages. Students learn Võro language on elementary level and learn to distinguish Seto, Mulgi and Tartu languages.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives an overview of South Estonian historical development, division, main features and contemporary situation. Through practical learning students acquire elementary skills of Võro language. By reading and listening to the texts, the students learn about the characteristics of the Seto, Mulgi and Tartu languages and learn to distinguish them all.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will know the historical development and contemporary situation of South Estonian and will have elementary skills of Võro (especially orthography, phonology, and inflection). Students understand Võro language and can translate simple sentences from Estonian into Võro; they know the main features of the Seto, Mulgi and Tartu languages and can distinguish them all.
